  "text": "7. The results of this study, taken together with previous findings [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] on the effect of reduced dynamic range, suggest that the performance of cochlear implant subjects is primarily limited by the small number (4-6) of channels received, and not by the small number of steps or reduced dynamic range. Therefore, more research is needed to find ways to increase the number of channels transmitted by cochlear implants.",
